# Godot 2D Survival (core)

Godot 4.x GDScript survivors-like game. Main scene: `res://survivors_game.tscn`. Orchestrator: root node `Game` + `game/game.gd`. Do not apply Unity/C# project rules here. Map/rationale: `AGENTS.md` (Korean). Game-logic comments in `.gd`: Korean one-line purpose (match existing style).

## Must not

- Do not rename the main scene root node `Game` or change `run/main_scene` without updating every `/root/Game` reference.
- Do not rename or remove `%`-referenced nodes in `survivors_game.tscn` (`%Player`, `%MapArena`, `%WeaponSelectMenu`, etc.) without updating all `%` usages.
- Do not change the group name `mobs`.
- Do not edit `.uid` files manually.
- Do not add per-variant mob scripts; all mob scenes must use `res://entities/mob/mob.gd`.

## Must (scene contract)

- Spawn position must come from `%MapArena.get_random_spawn_position(exclude_near_world)` (global coords, inside `arena_rect` minus `spawn_margin`; obstacle overlap retried on physics layer 1; optional world point excludes spawns within `player_clear_radius + mob_spawn_player_clear_extra`). Main play passes `%Player.global_position`. Main play (`survivors_game.tscn`) overrides `%MapArena` to 3× arena size; do not change main map size by editing `map_arena.gd` defaults only — update the scene instance override and `AGENTS.md`. Do not reintroduce `Player/Path2D` perimeter spawn without updating `AGENTS.md` and this rule.
- `Game.spawn_mob()` must acquire a `Mob` via `ScenePool.acquire(scene, parent, spawn_global_position)` (or instantiate fallback with the same position), then call `initialize_spawn_health()`.
- On mob death, kills must still reach `Game.register_kill()` via the existing `mob.gd` `_die()` path.

## When changing cross-scene paths

- If you change `/root/Game`, `/root/Game/Player`, or HUD paths, you must grep the repo and update every caller (`mob.gd`, `gun.gd`, `player.gd`, `exp_orb.gd`, etc.) in the same change.

## Pause / game start

- Do not start the spawn `Timer` until `_ensure_game_started()` runs (after initial weapon select flow completes).
- When `get_tree().paused` is true, do not advance the balance elapsed clock (`_is_balance_clock_running` in `game.gd`).

## Physics layers (do not change casually)

- Mob bodies: `collision_layer = 2`, `collision_mask = 3`.
- If you change mob layers, you must update weapon/projectile `collision_mask` consistently in the same PR.

## Display / camera / UI (see AGENTS.md)

- Viewport is HD 1280×720 in `project.godot`; UI layout uses FHD 1920×1080 via `UiViewportLayout` on HUD/menu roots — do not rescale UI offsets manually for HD.
- Player `Camera2D` zoom is `0.5` in `player.tscn`; change zoom there (not ad hoc in `player.gd`) and keep `checker_background.gd` in mind.
